One of the two security guards wounded during a shooting at Folweni High School early last month has succumbed to his injuries. Courtesy of #DSTV403 DURBAN - One of the two security guards wounded during a shooting at Folweni High School early last month succumbed to his injuries on Sunday. READ: Teacher gunned down at Durban school The guards came under fire from two armed suspects who forced entry into the school and made off with equipment. They were both hospitalised after sustaining gunshot wounds. READ: Union calls on government to allow teachers to arm themselves The incident happened shortly after the killing of a teacher on school grounds in the same area. It has once again raised questions about safety in schools.